The Payment Card Industry (PCI) Data Security Standards (DSS) is a global information security standardto prevent fraud through increased control of credit card data.
Organizations must follow PCI DSS standards if they accept payment cards from the major credit card brands such as Visa, MasterCard.
Compliance with PCI DSS is required for any organization that stores, processes, or transmits payment and cardholder data.

